    <stitle>ANTILOCK BRAKES/TRACTION CONTROL: BENDIX - PRINCIPLES, OPERATION AND SERVICE - INSTALL - REAR SENSOR
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>REAR SENSOR</title>
        <para>Install the sensor into retainer and sensor mounting block from the axle side in a horizontal position
            with the "cable end" of the sensor positioned as shown in
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0402908">Figure 8</hotlnk>, depending on suspension type. Push the sensor into the retainer
            as far as possible. The retainer is located in the sensor mounting block. No further adjustment is
            necessary.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0402908" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0402908" filename="../figg04/G0402908.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 8. Installing Rear Sensor</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
